3.title: Cumings and Goings
3.plot: Kayla returns from her vet conference with bad news: she has lost Maddie's dog (Jack). Not only does Maddie find out her dog is missing but is surprised when her brother (Joe) arrives on the door step saying he quit university but won't tell her why. Maddie and her boyfriend (Greg) are head over heels in love but when she starts to see the ghost of her dead fiancée (Marshall), she begins to doubt her sanity. 4.title: Fans of Private Parts
4.plot: Joe brings home a girl (Claudia) who is a huge fan of Maddie's work. Maddie likes Claudia so much that when Claudia announces she needs a new place to stay, Maddie suggests she moves in with them but Joe is already seeing someone else. Maddie suspects Greg is cheating on her after Jack (the dog) knocked his phone revealing a text message from a girl, while the ghost of her ex (Marshall) finally says goodbye. imdb.plot outline: All about Jack: Australia's Freshest New Comedy, a 27 minute Howling Wolf Films movie, features Australian actors Max Lewis and Paul James, who engage in crude joking behavior and clich''-filled soliloquies. The constantly changing plot mirrors the swift progression of emotions from ecstasy to sadness to indifference. Jack, as he is so aptly named, is given to the protagonist Maddie from her friend as a random gift. Maddie immediately befriends the brown mutt and looks to him for support and love. She claims to have named her new dog after her "hero," Jack Sparrow, the bad-boy conquistador of the fictional Pirates of the Caribbean movie series, played by Johnny Depp. What follows is a narrated flashback that exposes Maddie's failed marriage years ago tarnished by her ex-love Marshall's infidelity. In doing so, it illuminates her new dog Jack as a source of revitalization for Maddie from her earlier days of darkness.
imdb.title: All About Jack
plot: The first two episodes in the hit comedy series 'All about Jack'. Will Maddie be able to cope with the g-string wearing men that visit Kayla? A story of friendship, love, loss and one cute but naughty dog.::maxi lewis
